<section name="title" styleuri="/xusr/share/doc/styles_1060/style_title.xsl">
	<content>
		<name>dbxmlPutDocument</name>
		<text>Accessor to put an XML document into a Berkeley DBXML container</text>
	</content>
</section>

<section name="definition" styleuri="/xusr/share/doc/styles_1060/style_definition.xsl">
	<content>
		<module>urn:org:ten60:netkernel:mod:dbxml</module>
		<format>
		<sub name="format"/>
		</format>
		<returns>
<b>t</b>
		</returns>
		<syntax>
			<type><b>dbxmlPutDocument</b></type>
			<operand req="true">the document</operand>
			<operator req="true">the put specification document</operator>
			<target req="false">void response</target>
		</syntax>
		</content>
	<includes>

<include name="format" type="xml">
<instr>
      <type>dbxmlPutDocument</type>
	  <operand>mydoc.xml</operand>
      <operator>
		<dbxml>
			<name>mydocument</name>
			<container>mycontainer</container>
		</dbxml>
	  </operator>
    </instr>
</include>
</includes>
</section>

<section name="purpose" styleuri="/xusr/share/doc/styles_1060/style_basic.xsl">
	<content>
        <p>
		The <code>dbxmlPutDocument</code> accessor puts an XML document into a container in Berkeley DBXML.
		The put specification is provided as the <i>operator</i> argument and is
		an XML fragment.
		</p>
		<p>If successful the response is a voidAspect otherwise an exception is thrown.</p>
		<h3>Operator Format</h3>
		<p>
		The format for the operator is...
		</p>
		<sub name="config"/>
		<p>
		The <i>name</i> tag is required and will be used to identify the document in the container.  The <i>container</i> tag specifies
		the identity of the container in the BDBXML database into which the document is put.
		</p>
		<h3>Reference</h3>
		<ul>
		<li>Berkeley DBXML can be downloaded from <a href="http://www.sleepycat.com">Sleepycat Software</a>.</li>
		<li><a href="http://www.oracle.com/technology/documentation/berkeley-db/xml/java/index.html">Javadoc for BDBXML</a></li>
		</ul>		
	</content>
	<includes>
<include name="config" type="xml">
<dbxml>
	<name>someDocumentName</name>
	<container>someContainerName</container>
</dbxml>
</include>
	</includes>
</section>

